  "doc_id": "12872",
  "text": "It was reported in another study that when palmoplantar psoriasis and eczema share the same anatomical regions, they have similar clinical skin findings. It is shown that the most important histopathological distinction between these two diseases is multi focal parakeratosis [CITATION_1] . In the other study, while it is emphasized even the histopathological differentiation of psoriasis and eczema is very difficult, it has been suggested that these two diseases have similar clinical, histologic, biologic and therapeutic responses and there is an overlap condition [CITATION_2] .",
